SET 1 is acoustic Dead; this is the complete set.
Pigpen plays piano on Truckin, Ripple & New Speedway. Jerry switches to
electric guitar on New Speedway. David Nelson plays mandolin on Rosalie
McFall, Cold Jordan & Swing Low. Marmaduke adds bass vocals to Cold Jordan
and Swing Low. The introduction goes: "Good evening and welcome to the
Fillmore West. Tonight you're going to spend an evening with the Grateful
Dead."

reviews.review_text: 50 years This could be consideres the most important historical recording of the dead. No boards, just this killer audience and free to the world thanks to the archive. Peace

Thank you This is awesome documentation of a very loving transfer.  This show is epic in Dead history.  The origin of Truckin', Ripple, Brokedown Palace, Operator. Wow, just wow.  So cool to see some of my favorite dead songs be born and to hear them so clearly for the first time.  I really appreciate the work you put into this and am glad to see an epic collection be in good hands (and now in my ears).

Awesome Audience Recording! Thanks! The acoustic material is great! effort is appreciated if you think of all the people and steps this took too get to this moment! Oh yeah...
Support The Archive!
